Even before I submitted my first photo in Unsplash, I always used to look at these epic misty forest shots with awe. Then I managed to do my own. Heck, my most popular is one of them. Sometimes we set our own limits and we become our own worst enemies. The past 4-5 years of my life, it became very clear to me that one has to define his own life. Push boundaries, try the unthinkable and challenge one’s self. 

P.S. I love misty forest shots.

I wouldn’t have called this a perfect day, at least not by most standards. Dark, cold, and a bit snowy for fall. It wasn’t blue skies and sunny to say the least.

Despite everything being a bit “messy” it was a prefect day for photography and it led to amazing shots like this one.

Sometimes just because things aren’t “perfect” doesn’t mean they can’t be perfect 😉

It could be anything. An old camera, a place, your house, your dog and ultimately your self. Just let go. It took me years to realize it, and had to go through some educating moments and situations to understand it. That’s what I am being reminded every time I take one of these nature landscape photos. Letting go brought me to the mountains. Letting go brought me here.
